Explore the stunning Malka Mari National , situated along the Dawa River on the Kenya-Ethiopia border. It is approximately 1,500 square kilometres (370,000 acres) in size. It is accessible via the Mandera Airport, and is probably the least visited national park in the nation.

The city lies along the Nairobi Nakuru Highway, a distance of 160 kilometers from Nairobi, the capital of Kenya. It is the third largest city and fourth largest urban centre by metropolitan area in Kenya, behind Nairobi, Mombasa and Kisumu respectively. It lies about 1,850 m above sea level.

Moyale is the main border post on the Nairobi-Addis Ababa road, lying north of the Dide Galgalu Desert. It is known for its traditional architecture. Moyale is a mainly Borona market town on the border between Ethiopia and Kenya.

Namanga is possibly Kenya's busiest border town and is set in the Rift Valley of Kenya. Namanga is en-route to the Amboseli National Park, which is home to some of the region's oldest elephants. A game reserve since 1899, Amboseli became a national park in 1974.

Explore Kitale,it's is an agricultural town in northern Rift Valley Kenya situated between Mount Elgon and the Cherangany Hills at an elevation of around 1,900 metres (6,200 ft).

Embu is home to Mwea National Reserve. Best known for the diversity of bird species in the reserve. Ancient caves are also found in Embu, commonly referred to as 'Ngurunga ya Ngai' by the Embu natives.

About.title: About Our Travel Agency
About.description: At our travel agency, we are passionate about creating unforgettable travel experiences for our clients. Whether you are looking for a relaxing beach vacation or an adventure-packed journey through a new country, we have you covered. Our team of experienced travel agents are dedicated to helping you plan the perfect trip, from start to finish. We work with a network of trusted partners and vendors to ensure that you receive the best possible accommodations, activities, and amenities for your budget. Contact us today to start planning your next adventure!
